transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Thanks for calling Viagra, Clint speaking. How can I help you?

Speaker 2: I need to cancel my subscription.

Speaker 1: Is your name Mark?

Speaker 2: Yep.

Speaker 1: Alrighty, Mark, I do see you're a VIP member here with us. Do you mind telling me why you want to cancel your Viagra today?

Speaker 2: I just don't need them.

Speaker 1: Okay, and you're kind of getting them too fast, because you can always order this as needed.

Speaker 2: No, I mean, I don't know. Maybe it's needed, but you guys auto-shipped them to me and I never signed up for an auto-ship.

Speaker 1: Yeah, see, that only happens if you don't set it up for the days and months you want it to come out.

Speaker 2: Unless you don't choose the as-needed option, it will go up that way, but it doesn't have to be that way, sir.

Speaker 1: Okay, well, you know, I probably don't...

Speaker 2: I mean, the amount that I'm using right now, it's not even probably worth having, so...

Speaker 1: Yeah, so just maybe put me as needed.

Speaker 2: Okay, yeah, so basically in the next about five months here, we won't bill you or send you anything.

Speaker 1: You're going to have to give us a call to receive anything, okay?

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: I'm not going to see any charges or anything anymore, right?

Speaker 2: No, sir, and you're going to call us for your orders in the next five months.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: If you have more time or if you ever want to cancel, you can always call at any moment.

Speaker 1: Okay, all right. Thank you.

Speaker 2: You're welcome.
